OL,6,FIn a letter to constituents, Shabana
OL,7,FMahmood said she was "profoundly
OL,8,Fconcerned" by the legislation, not
OL,9,Fjust for religious reasons but because
OL,10,Fit could create a "slippery slope
OL,11,Ftowards death on demand", the Observer
OL,12,Freported.
OL,14,FMs Mahmood has previously made clear
OL,15,Fshe would vote against the Bill
OL,16,Falongside Health Secretary Wes
OL,17,FStreeting, who faced a backlash after
OL,18,Fsuggesting the changes would cost the
OL,19,FNHS more.
