OL,6,FBut her letter to voters goes further,
OL,7,Fstating: "Sadly, recent scandals `
OL,8,Fsuch as Hillsborough, infected blood
OL,9,Fand the Post Office Horizon ` have
OL,10,Freminded us that the state and those
OL,11,Facting on its behalf are not always
OL,12,Fbenign.
OL,14,F"I have always held the view that, for
OL,15,Fthis reason, the state should serve a
OL,16,Fclear role. It should protect and
OL,17,Fpreserve life, not take it away. The
OL,18,Fstate should never offer death as a
OL,19,Fservice."
