OL,6,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer has
OL,7,Fdeclined to say whether he will back
OL,8,Fthe Bill, arguing that he does not
OL,9,Fwant to pressure MPs. Members will be
OL,10,Fgiven a free vote to act according to
OL,11,Ftheir personal beliefs, rather than in
OL,12,Fline with party policy.
OL,14,FBut prominent figures including former
OL,15,Fprime minister Gordon Brown have
OL,16,Fvoiced opposition to the legislation.
