OL,6,FMs Mahmood, Mr Streeting and Education
OL,7,FSecretary Bridget Phillipson have said
OL,8,Fthey will vote against the Bill while
OL,9,Fcare minister Stephen Kinnock said he
OL,10,Fsupports it.
OL,12,FProponents argue existing legislation
OL,13,Ffails to respect patient autonomy and
OL,14,Fdiscriminates financially between
OL,15,Fthose who can afford to travel abroad
OL,16,Fto end their lives within the law and
OL,17,Fthose who cannot.
