OL,6,FLeading barristers including former
OL,7,Fdirector of public prosecutions Sir
OL,8,FMax Hill KC have spoken in favour of
OL,9,Fthe Bill, saying it would offer better
OL,10,Fsafeguards than the current system
OL,11,Fthrough a process involving two
OL,12,Fdoctors and a judge.
OL,14,FLabour MP Kim Leadbeater has described
OL,15,Fher Bill as the most "robust" in the
OL,16,Fworld, with "three layers of scrutiny"
OL,17,Fin the form of a sign-off by two
OL,18,Fdoctors and a High Court judge.
